  "prompt": "What happens if the incumbent president dies on inauguration day of the new president-elect?",
  "response": "If the incumbent president dies on Inauguration Day before the president-elect is sworn in, the following would occur:\n\n1. The Vice President-elect would be sworn in as President according to the Presidential Succession Act and the 20th Amendment to the U.S. Constitution.\n\n2. If for some reason the Vice President-elect cannot serve, the line of succession would follow the order established in the Presidential Succession Act: Speaker of the House, President Pro Tempore of the Senate, and then Cabinet members in a specific order.\n\n3. If the president-elect dies before being sworn in, the Vice President-elect would become President at noon on Inauguration Day.\n\nThe 20th Amendment specifically addresses presidential succession and ensures a smooth transition of power in such scenarios, guaranteeing that there is always a legitimate president in office.",
